%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22TikTok%20is%20splitting%20its%20US%20staff%20into%20different%20companies%20as%20it%20prepares%20for%20a%20sale%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226461%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TikTok%20logo%20in%20front%20of%20a%20United%20States%20flag%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69607805832e0ef1ead774bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224307%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EIsmail%20Aslandag%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETikTok%20told%20some%20US%20staff%20that%20they%20will%20not%20work%20under%20a%20new%20joint%20venture%20run%20by%20Oracle%20and%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInstead%2C%20they'll%20switch%20to%20a%20new%20entity%20set%20up%20for%20workers%20in%20global%20business%20lines%2C%20like%20e-commerce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20move%20showcases%20how%20ByteDance%20will%20stay%20in%20charge%20of%20key%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20business%20after%20a%20sale.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20is%20preparing%20to%20carve%20off%20parts%20of%20its%20US%20business%2C%20but%20not%20all%20US%20workers%20are%20joining%20the%20new%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20US%20staff%20were%20told%20this%20week%20that%20they%20will%20not%20work%20for%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-reaches-deal-with-investors-on-its-us-business-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoint%20venture%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecalled%20TikTok%20USDS%20Joint%20Venture%20LLC%2C%20led%20by%20managing%20investors%20Oracle%2C%20Silver%20Lake%2C%20and%20MGX.%20Instead%2C%20they%20will%20work%20for%20a%20separate%20TikTok%20global%20entity%20that%20will%20remain%20under%20ByteDance's%20ownership%2C%20called%20TT%20Commerce%20%26amp%3B%20Global%20Services%20LLC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20change%2C%20outlined%20in%20a%20memo%20sent%20to%20impacted%20employees%2C%20includes%20workers%20who%20focus%20on%20US%20products%20that%20will%20remain%20tied%20to%20TikTok's%20global%20operations%20after%20the%20sale%20closes.%20In%20December%2C%20TikTok's%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-reaches-deal-with-investors-on-its-us-business-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShou%20Chew%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20staff%20those%20business%20lines%20would%20include%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20commercial%20activities%2C%20including%20e-commerce%2C%20advertising%2C%20and%20marketing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20US%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20those%20focused%20on%20data%20protection%20or%20algorithm%20security%2C%20would%20work%20under%20the%20USDS%20Joint%20Venture%20entity%2C%20according%20to%20Chew's%20memo.%20He%20said%20the%20deal%20would%20close%20on%20January%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20and%20ByteDance%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%20about%20the%20staffing%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2224f9e0ca-8fc0-4aa0-ab3b-8384dfa04d76%5C%22%3EWhy%20TikTok%20US%20is%20splitting%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20proposed%20TikTok%20deal%20goes%20through%2C%20Oracle%2C%20MGX%2C%20and%20Silver%20Lake%20would%20each%20own%2015%25%20of%20the%20new%20US%20joint%20venture.%20Affiliates%20of%20existing%20ByteDance%20investors%20would%20get%20around%2030%25.%20Five%20percent%20would%20go%20to%20an%20unnamed%20group%20of%20new%20investors%2C%20and%20ByteDance%20would%20keep%20just%20under%2020%25%20of%20the%20business%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20ownership%20requirements%20of%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-passes-tiktok-ban-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edivestment%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20sparked%20the%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Protecting%20Americans%20from%20Foreign%20Adversary%20Controlled%20Applications%20Act%2C%20requires%20companies%20based%20in%20countries%20the%20US%20has%20deemed%20a%20foreign%20adversary%20to%20divest%20from%20their%20US%20assets%20or%20face%20hefty%20fines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECongress%20called%20out%20TikTok%20and%20China-based%20ByteDance%20in%20the%20law's%20text.%20TikTok%20challenged%20the%20law%20in%20court%20but%20lost%20its%20case%20in%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20last%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20allowed%20the%20app%20to%20continue%20to%20operate%20last%20year%20via%20a%20series%20of%20executive%20orders%20as%20his%20administration%20worked%20with%20TikTok%20and%20prospective%20buyers%20on%20a%20potential%20deal.%20In%20September%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-signs-off-tiktok-deal-new-owners-oracle-data-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWhite%20House%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20a%20deal%20had%20been%20reached%2C%20which%20Vice%20President%20JD%20Vance%20said%20would%20value%20TikTok%20US%20at%20around%20%2414%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-splitting-us-staff-entities-divestment-ecommerce-tt-commerce-global-2026-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1767933768000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69607a7304eda4732f2ec200%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-splitting-us-staff-entities-divestment-ecommerce-tt-commerce-global-2026-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TikTok%20told%20some%20US%20staff%20that%20they%20will%20work%20for%20a%20new%20global%20entity%20that%20is%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20new%20joint%20venture%20run%20by%20Oracle%20and%20others.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dwhateley%40businessinsider.com%20(Dan%20Whateley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-splitting-us-staff-entities-divestment-ecommerce-tt-commerce-global-2026-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'C