y.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-defense-firms-buybacks-dividends-lmt-gd-noc-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump%20said%20he%20would%20ban%20buybacks%20and%20dividends%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20demanded%20that%20executive%20salaries%20be%20capped%20at%20%245%20million%20until%20military%20equipment%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emanufacturing%20improves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20appeared%20to%20be%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-era-america-capitalism-socialist-trump-economy-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20broader%20push%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20assert%20more%20government%20control%20over%20corporations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20an%20accompanying%20executive%20order%2C%20also%20issued%20Wednesday%20night%2C%20offered%20more%20nuance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20order%20also%20begins%20with%20a%20lengthy%20complaint%20criticizing%20defense%20contractors%20for%20pursuing%20%26quot%3Bmore%20lucrative%20contracts%26quot%3B%20while%20delivering%20late%20and%20over%20budget%20on%20existing%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20eleventh%20paragraph%2C%20the%20executive%20order%20explains%20how%20the%20Defense%20Department%20would%20enforce%20Trump's%20priorities%3A%20Through%20the%20enforcement%20of%20future%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20requires%20Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20to%20ensure%20that%2C%20in%20future%20military%20contracts%2C%20the%20executive%20compensation%20for%20contractors%20isn't%20tied%20to%20%26quot%3Bshort-term%20financial%20metrics%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20to%20increased%20production%2C%20delivery%20time%2C%20and%20other%20improvements%20%26quot%3Brequired%20to%20rapidly%20expand%20our%20United%20States%20stockpiles%20and%20capabilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20order%20doesn't%20include%20the%20%245%20million%20salary%20cap%20that%20he%20posted%20about%20on%20social%20media.%20Instead%2C%20it%20empowers%20Hegseth%20to%20require%20contractors%20to%20cap%20executive%20base%20salaries%20at%20existing%20levels%20if%20they%20don't%20meet%20the%20Defense%20Department%20secretary's%20performance%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20requires%20the%20government's%20defense%20contracts%20to%20forbid%20companies%20from%20issuing%20stock%20buybacks%20and%20other%20payments%20to%20shareholders%20during%20periods%20when%20they%20have%20not%20met%20Hegseth's%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20order%20gives%20Hegseth%20wide%20discretion%20to%20define%20the%20%26quot%3Bperiod%20of%20underperformance%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Binsufficient%20prioritization%20of%20the%20contract%26quot%3B%20where%20those%20restrictions%20kick%20in.%20The%20executive%20order%20says%20those%20definitions%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bdetermined%20by%20the%20Secretary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arrangement%20%26quot%3Bputs%20the%20Secretary%20of%20War%20into%20the%20shoes%20of%20the%20Securities%20Exchange%20Commission%26quot%3B%20by%20giving%20Hegseth%20the%20power%20to%20determine%20how%20the%20companies%20can%20handle%20their%20finances%2C%20said%20Harold%20Koh%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20national%20security%20law%20at%20Yale%20Law%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20policy%20with%20regard%20to%20corporate%20distributions%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20corporate%20finance%2C%20Koh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20defense%20performance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20order%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20is%20a%20directive%20on%20how%20the%20Defense%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20Trump%20administration%20calls%20the%20War%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20should%20treat%20military%20contracts%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20can%20accept%20those%20terms%2C%20or%20lose%20out%20on%20contracts%20that%20could%20instead%20go%20to%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20a%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20contractor%20acc